<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,1399,553,686]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<bibRefCitation author="Nesi N." box="[189,387,553,579]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref270498" refString="Nesi N. 2012. Systematique et Phylogeographie des Chauves-Souris africaines de la Sous-Famille des Epomophorinae (Chiroptera, Pteropodidae). PhD Thesis, Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris." type="book" year="2012">Nesi (2012: 179)</bibRefCitation>
reported a single specimen of this species from Kitombongo (Upemba National Park, Haut-Lomami Province). 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergmans" box="[488,689,589,615]" firstAuthor="Bergmans" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="238 - 240" refId="ref257583" refString="Bergmans W. 2013. Epomophorus anselli Ansell's Epauletted Fruit Bat. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 238 - 240. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013">Bergmans (2013)</bibRefCitation>
mentions this species from two (possibly three) localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[189,276,624,650]" name="Malawi" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Malawi</collectingCountry>
and one in southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[558,664,624,650]" name="Tanzania" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
. Based on these data, the SDM map suggests that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergmans &amp; Van Strien" authorityYear="2004" box="[1220,1326,624,650]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anselli">
<emphasis box="[1220,1326,624,650]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">E. anselli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might occur from southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[476,535,659,685]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">DRC</collectingCountry>
over northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[753,840,659,685]" name="Zambia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Zambia</collectingCountry>
to southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1038,1140,659,685]" name="Tanzania" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1304,1394,659,685]" name="Malawi" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Malawi</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
